# Enforce LF line endings on checkout for ALL text files, regardless of OS.
#
# Rationale: Qalam's determinism contract requires bit-identical output across
# Linux, macOS, and Windows. Any data file embedded via `include_str!` or
# `include_bytes!` must therefore have identical bytes on every platform.
# Without this, Git's default `autocrlf` on Windows would convert LF to CRLF
# on checkout and silently break cross-OS reproducibility.

* text=auto eol=lf

# Explicit overrides for known binary types (in case of future additions).
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.zip binary
*.fst binary
